========,3,Library.
The library was originally funded by tycoon and entrepreneur Andrew Carnegie in 1906.
In 2005, the library loaned more than 238,000 items to its 20,000 cardholders.
Total holdings in 2005 were over 91,000 volumes with over 210 periodical subscriptions.
From 2016-2017 the library underwent a major renovation, fixing the crumbling foundation of the library building.
The library temporarily moved out to the former location of Bill's Lockeroom on Shoop Avenue until mid April 2017 before moving back in to the original library building on Elm Street.
